channel.title: Last question
channel.description:
Yes, I've only asked for help once, but.
Well I changed my starting, thought i changed it to falador, but its somewhere off the coast of karajima :|
Could anyone give me the code to input to make it fally? (Not center, but south where you fight white knights etc) Thanks if you can, Thanks anyway if its not allowed.

item.title: Last question
item.dc:creator: @super_OLDACCOUNT super_OLDACCOUNT
item.description:
@super_OLDACCOUNT wrote:

[quote=“TeleNubby, post:4, topic:186607”][quote author=super_ link=topic=249072.msg2090180#msg2090180 date=1204774085]
write a client that, when the x and y positions of the current entity change, logs them to a file or to the command prompt, and find the coordinates of the place you want to go to
[/quote]Hm. Wouldn’t that be kind of pointless if you don’t know where those coordinates are on the RS Map? Outputting to a file with just x & y coordinates without any labels/descriptions is pointless, especially because those coords change everytime you take a step. Just one huge output file with lots of coords. Unless I missed something?[/quote]
it would come out something like:

[entity-pos change] x: 0000, y: 0000

and you would just use the ones of the last coordinate

item.description:
@MontyBoy wrote:

[quote=“TeleNubby, post:2, topic:186607”]Go to Falador in-game.
Write down the coordinates of the spot you want to start at.
Open up player.java.
Replace old coordinates with new coordinates.
Save. Compile. Run.[/quote]

Which coords do i replace. when i Ctrl +f “CurrentX / y” alot come up, and when i found the one i recently edited, changed it nothing happened,
